TheGreatEscape.cpp is an AI program I wrote for a world-wide AI contest host by www.codingame.com. It finally ranks at 12/1133. It uses enhanced-BFS to find safest and shortest path to destination and uses customized Minimax algorithm to decide when and how to place the walls to delay opponents and protect myself. Video demo of this game and my AI is available on www.luminghub.com

Aircraft object hierarchy is the core object hierarchy in my 3D game - Air Battle. Video demo of this game is available on www.luminghub.com

Mesh is the mesh data structure I used in my modern OpenGL game engine.

loopInv.cpp and GCRA.cpp are loop invariant and graph-coloring register allocation LLVM passes.

sortLinkedList.cpp is a merge sort algorithm for sorting singly-linked list.

